726606f-a.title: Queens: Roosevelt Avenue - 114th Street
726606f-a.text:
Flushing Meadow Park (ueens): Viewing north across the
marshland and an ash road leading to the dump hills on the western
edge of the park, seen from near Roosevelt Avenue and 114th Street.
This area later became part of the New York World's Fair grounds
ef 1939-40.
October, 1935
Views 1,2,3
P. L. Sperr

725805f-b.title: Queens: 114th Street - Roosevelt Avenue
725805f-b.text:
114th Street, north fro Roosevelt Avenue, from underneath
the B.M.T.-I.R.T. elevated. The area on the right was later
transformed into part of the World's Fair grounds of 1939-40.
P. L. Sperr  View 1: September 30, 1935
NO REPRODUCTIONS  View 2: May 30, 1938
View 3r June 23, 1940
